1
00:01:26,060 --> 00:01:28,060
[Under the Moonlight]

2
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:30,060
[Adapted from the novel
"Jin Nang" by Shui He]

3
00:01:30,820 --> 00:01:33,000
[Episode 7]

4
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:34,760
Tell me what really happened.

5
00:01:34,950 --> 00:01:36,190
If you didn't commit murder,

6
00:01:36,190 --> 00:01:37,870
you can explain it to yamen.

7
00:01:38,510 --> 00:01:41,440
But I can't...

8
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:45,270
Grab your stuff and flee.

9
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:47,760
Come on, leave.

10
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:49,720
Where to go, Mother?

11
00:01:49,910 --> 00:01:50,550
They haven't wanted

12
00:01:50,550 --> 00:01:51,550
you yet.

13
00:01:51,550 --> 00:01:52,760
Leave Linfen now.

14
00:01:52,870 --> 00:01:54,120
How will you make a living if I leave?

15
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,480
I can't leave you alone.

16
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:56,510
Don't worry about me.

17
00:01:56,510 --> 00:01:57,870
I can live on my own.

18
00:01:58,160 --> 00:01:58,950
You must stay alive.

19
00:01:58,950 --> 00:01:59,950
That's all I want.

20
00:01:59,950 --> 00:02:02,000
Leave. Leave now!

21
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:02,950
Hurry!

22
00:02:05,630 --> 00:02:06,440
Mother,

23
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:09,110
sorry for this.

24
00:02:11,110 --> 00:02:12,110
I'll come back

25
00:02:12,750 --> 00:02:14,190
to take care of you
a couple of years later.

26
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:18,000
Feng Erlang, you can't leave.

27
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:18,630
Come with us.

28
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:21,080
Come!

29
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:22,750
Erlang,

30
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:23,830
Erlang, run!

31
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,320
Run!

32
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:25,750
Mother!

33
00:02:25,750 --> 00:02:26,320
Run, Erlang!

34
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:27,270
Go arrest him!

35
00:02:27,830 --> 00:02:30,000
You can't go. Stop!

36
00:02:30,550 --> 00:02:31,390
Don't fight here.

37
00:02:31,390 --> 00:02:32,240
You women don't fight.

38
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,110
This is so rude.

39
00:02:33,110 --> 00:02:34,190
Only we men fight.

40
00:02:34,190 --> 00:02:35,110
Chase him!

41
00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:36,550
Go, go, go.

42
00:02:36,550 --> 00:02:37,670
Protect yourself.

43
00:02:37,830 --> 00:02:39,960
Don't go! Stop.

44
00:02:53,670 --> 00:02:54,320
Stop!

45
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,470
Stop!

46
00:02:58,720 --> 00:02:59,630
He is over there!

47
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:12,390
Look what you did!

48
00:03:12,390 --> 00:03:12,880
Sorry.

49
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:13,830
Damn you!

50
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:21,320
Freeze!

51
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:23,270
Young Master.

52
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,080
Lian Shu, compensate her!

53
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:36,160
Compensate me!

54
00:03:50,270 --> 00:03:50,880
Go!

55
00:04:06,030 --> 00:04:08,240
Young Master.

56
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:08,670
Quick!

57
00:04:08,670 --> 00:04:10,160
Get a rope to strap him. Come on!

58
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:11,550
Rope.

59
00:04:11,630 --> 00:04:12,750
Young Master, be careful!

60
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:14,240
Hello.

61
00:04:16,550 --> 00:04:17,640
Young Master, hang in there.

62
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:19,200
I can't!

63
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:20,320
Hang in there.

64
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,830
Can anyone give me a rope

65
00:04:22,830 --> 00:04:24,070
to do us a favor?

66
00:04:24,070 --> 00:04:25,600
We yamen officers
are arresting the suspect.

67
00:04:25,950 --> 00:04:28,000
Please bring a rope here.

68
00:04:28,070 --> 00:04:29,000
Here!

69
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:29,320
Where's the suspect?

70
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:29,880
Where is it?

71
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:30,950
It's in there.

72
00:04:30,950 --> 00:04:31,830
Hurry!

73
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,270
Go, go, go.

74
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,440
Quick!

75
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:37,880
Tie him up tightly!

76
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:39,350
Make sure he can't escape.

77
00:04:39,350 --> 00:04:41,440
Tie him up tightly!

78
00:04:41,550 --> 00:04:42,760
Make sure he has no chance to escape.

79
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:44,070
Tie him up tightly!

80
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:45,640
Harder!

81
00:04:46,230 --> 00:04:47,350
You tied the wrong one.

82
00:04:47,510 --> 00:04:49,440
He's my Young Master.

83
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:50,550
Young Master, just a minute.

84
00:04:50,550 --> 00:04:51,720
They'll untie you now.

85
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,070
Quick! Untie him!

86
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,350
Move aside!

87
00:04:56,550 --> 00:04:57,510
Quick, untie him!

88
00:04:57,510 --> 00:04:58,790
Untie my Young Master.

89
00:04:58,790 --> 00:04:59,480
Untie him.

90
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:00,320
Do it now!

91
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:02,040
Hurry, do it.

92
00:05:02,350 --> 00:05:03,040
Hurry.

93
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,760
Untie him. Come on.

94
00:05:05,110 --> 00:05:06,390
Help me up!

95
00:05:06,390 --> 00:05:07,790
Help me up please.

96
00:05:07,790 --> 00:05:08,440
Go!

97
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:09,880
Hurry!

98
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:26,350
Young Master,

99
00:05:26,670 --> 00:05:28,040
your clothes is dirty.

100
00:05:28,390 --> 00:05:29,480
It's dusty.

101
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:30,480
Sorry for this, Young Master.

102
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:31,550
You pat me too harder.

103
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:43,110
Is your ankle okay?

104
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:44,440
I'm alright.

105
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:46,670
Here, come.

106
00:05:47,790 --> 00:05:48,600
Why?

107
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,040
I'll carry you.

108
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:50,950
Come on up.

109
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,040
I'll walk.

110
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:53,920
You're injured.

111
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,160
Don't be stubborn. Let me carry you.

112
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:57,440
No need.

113
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,160
Come on.

114
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,480
Sir, stop.

115
00:06:04,350 --> 00:06:05,160
Please stop.

116
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:08,270
Sir,

117
00:06:10,110 --> 00:06:11,480
can you take us

118
00:06:11,550 --> 00:06:12,790
to yamen please?

119
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:16,390
Come on up.

120
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:17,670
Thank you.

121
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:22,600
Come on, I'll help you.

122
00:06:24,390 --> 00:06:24,880
You?

123
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,160
You can come up too.

124
00:06:32,110 --> 00:06:32,920
Young Master.

125
00:06:38,510 --> 00:06:39,440
Sit tight.

126
00:07:09,270 --> 00:07:10,200
What happened to your hand?

127
00:07:10,670 --> 00:07:12,200
It's okay. I'm fine.

128
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:15,000
Young Master.

129
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,790
You're badly hurt.

130
00:07:16,790 --> 00:07:17,550
Just a small injury.

131
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:18,950
It's serious.

132
00:07:18,950 --> 00:07:20,200
You're bleeding.

133
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,480
It doesn't matter.

134
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:22,600
Not need to get worried.

135
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:23,760
It's not a big deal.

136
00:07:28,270 --> 00:07:29,070
Sir,

137
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,000
can I buy a jar

138
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,160
of your liquor?

139
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:32,200
Okay, just take it.

140
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:32,920
Thank you.

141
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:36,440
Lian Shu,

142
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:37,670
move your Young Master's hand

143
00:07:37,670 --> 00:07:38,510
closer to me.

144
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,670
It hurts.

145
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:42,670
You've to endure it.

146
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:44,600
It's not a big deal.

147
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:51,270
Have my bones got hurt?

148
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:56,390
Stop!

149
00:07:57,230 --> 00:07:58,950
Just stop!

150
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:01,510
Don't touch it!

151
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,550
A small wound.

152
00:08:04,390 --> 00:08:05,320
Eatting some nutritious food

153
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:06,600
will help you get recovered soon.

154
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:10,790
Gently please!

155
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:15,270
Gently,

156
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:19,230
please.

157
00:08:23,790 --> 00:08:24,600
You!

158
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:26,830
Thanks a lot.

159
00:08:37,590 --> 00:08:38,790
Get off.

160
00:08:41,150 --> 00:08:41,910
Come on.

161
00:08:41,910 --> 00:08:42,670
What are you doing?

162
00:08:42,710 --> 00:08:43,520
You ankle is sprained.

163
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:44,440
I'll help you come down.

164
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,000
Get away. Don't touch me.

165
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,080
Didn't you just touch my hand?

166
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:47,640
Don't worry.

167
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:24,760
Maintain order!

168
00:09:30,590 --> 00:09:31,710
Bring the suspect over.

169
00:09:41,030 --> 00:09:41,960
Feng Erlang!

170
00:09:42,350 --> 00:09:44,080
Why did you kill Meng Qiaosheng?

171
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,150
I didn't kill him.

172
00:09:46,150 --> 00:09:48,030
You rented a boat five days ago,

173
00:09:48,550 --> 00:09:50,710
killed him on it,
threw his body in the river

174
00:09:50,710 --> 00:09:51,910
and abandoned the boat.

175
00:09:51,910 --> 00:09:53,110
Did you do it or not?

176
00:09:53,110 --> 00:09:53,910
I didn't do it.

177
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,030
There was a witness

178
00:09:55,030 --> 00:09:56,520
of you renting the boat.

179
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:57,710
Yes, I rent it.

180
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,670
Renting it isn't against the law, is it?

181
00:10:02,030 --> 00:10:04,080
And I didn't know Meng Qiaosheng.

182
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,880
Are you sure of that?

183
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:13,200
Then his hairpin was found

184
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:15,080
on the boat you rent?

185
00:10:17,790 --> 00:10:19,150
I didn't kill him anyway.

186
00:10:19,150 --> 00:10:20,640
So why were you running away

187
00:10:20,670 --> 00:10:22,520
when you saw yamen officers?

188
00:10:22,710 --> 00:10:24,520
I feared I couldn't explain clearly
what happened.

189
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:26,470
Your lie

190
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:28,320
proves you're guilty.

191
00:10:32,550 --> 00:10:33,440
Yeah,

192
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:35,760
I rented the boat

193
00:10:36,150 --> 00:10:37,590
and also met Meng Qiaosheng.

194
00:10:38,230 --> 00:10:39,670
But I didn't kill him.

195
00:10:39,710 --> 00:10:41,470
Was he on your boat at that day?

196
00:10:41,470 --> 00:10:41,910
Yes.

197
00:10:41,910 --> 00:10:42,790
How come he was on it?

198
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,280
He got it on himself.

199
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:47,400
It's a lie!

200
00:10:52,110 --> 00:10:54,550
I abducted him to the boat.

201
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:55,440
Why did you do that?

202
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:56,710
Where did you abduct him?

203
00:10:59,000 --> 00:10:59,790
I don't know.

204
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:00,960
You don't now?

205
00:11:01,350 --> 00:11:03,350
You know it as you killed him.

206
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:06,350
I didn't kill him!

207
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:09,470
I...

208
00:11:10,350 --> 00:11:11,470
I punched him a few times.

209
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:13,350
Maybe I did it too hard.

210
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:15,150
I just kicked him.

211
00:11:15,150 --> 00:11:15,960
Feng Erlang,

212
00:11:17,670 --> 00:11:19,520
you beat him till he was badly injured

213
00:11:19,590 --> 00:11:21,350
and then threw this body into the river.

214
00:11:21,350 --> 00:11:22,670
So you commited murder.

215
00:11:22,670 --> 00:11:24,280
He jumped into it

216
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:26,080
and was fine when he swam away.

217
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,230
Feng Erlang,

218
00:11:37,230 --> 00:11:38,590
so you've admitted

219
00:11:40,150 --> 00:11:42,440
the kidnapping of Meng Qiaosheng.

220
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,710
And you beat him

221
00:11:44,710 --> 00:11:46,110
and he fell into the water.

222
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:47,200
Is it true?

223
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:50,910
Yes.

224
00:11:52,110 --> 00:11:53,440
Meng Qiaosheng died from drowning

225
00:11:53,710 --> 00:11:55,470
according to the examination
of the post-mortem examiner.

226
00:11:55,760 --> 00:11:57,320
You kidnapped him to the boat,

227
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:59,470
so you're guilty of his death.

228
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:00,670
Do you stilll defend yourself?

229
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:06,880
No.

230
00:12:07,910 --> 00:12:09,400
You'll be sentenced to death for murder.

231
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:13,000
Feng Erlang, you admit the crime, right?

232
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:24,080
Shall we close the case?

233
00:12:30,670 --> 00:12:32,110
Do you think it can be closed?

234
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:36,280
He already admitted it himself.

235
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:38,230
You're the the county magistrate.

236
00:12:38,230 --> 00:12:39,710
Better not waste the time

237
00:12:39,710 --> 00:12:41,400
on this trivial case.

238
00:12:43,230 --> 00:12:44,110
It won't waste the time.

239
00:12:44,760 --> 00:12:45,840
What do you think about the case?

240
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:48,670
Feng Erlang hid

241
00:12:48,670 --> 00:12:49,910
the most critical information.

242
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:51,230
Yes.

243
00:12:52,110 --> 00:12:53,840
It must be very important to him.

244
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,080
To conceal it,

245
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,960
he even committed the murder.

246
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:58,640
We need to find out

247
00:12:58,640 --> 00:12:59,320
where he kidnapped

248
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,550
Meng Qiaosheng.

249
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:01,470
Then

250
00:13:01,470 --> 00:13:02,840
the truth will be revealed.

251
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:06,200
He has admitted the crime.

252
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:08,150
Why do you exculpate for him?

253
00:13:10,710 --> 00:13:11,880
What do you think?

254
00:13:12,790 --> 00:13:13,880
Feng Erlang and Meng Qiaosheng

255
00:13:13,910 --> 00:13:15,230
had the feud

256
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:17,000
because of Meing Hongying.

257
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,200
We need to find the clue

258
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,910
from her.

259
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:32,910
You!

260
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:37,000
Why are you wearing a dress?

261
00:13:38,550 --> 00:13:39,960
Oh, are you

262
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:41,320
going to...

263
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:43,030
I'm going to
the Mei family's house on the case.

264
00:13:43,350 --> 00:13:44,760
No need to go with me.

265
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:46,440
I'm going to meet
the womenfolk of their family.

266
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:47,550
So I wear the dress

267
00:13:47,550 --> 00:13:49,520
as the maid of Mr. Han.

268
00:13:50,030 --> 00:13:51,440
You're a man.

269
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,080
It's improper for you to come.

270
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:52,790
Oh, no.

271
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:54,440
You go there as a maid.

272
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:57,320
I can go as a servant.

273
00:14:04,710 --> 00:14:05,880
Young Master, better not do this.

274
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:07,440
My clothes size is smaller.

275
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:17,910
Watch your words and behave yourself

276
00:14:17,910 --> 00:14:19,350
at their home.

277
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:20,200
No worries.

278
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,710
I'll keep silent.

279
00:14:39,470 --> 00:14:40,350
Who are you?

280
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:42,030
We are servants

281
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:43,230
of yamen.

282
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:44,080
Wanna inquire of Mei Hongying

283
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:45,280
about something.

284
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:46,150
Hongying?

285
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:47,670
What's the matter?

286
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:51,000
Is she at home?

287
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:54,440
She can't meet you now.

288
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:56,440
Honey!

289
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:58,440
What's up?

290
00:14:58,910 --> 00:14:59,960
What are you doing? Hongying!

291
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:01,590
Honey!

292
00:15:01,590 --> 00:15:02,000
What's up?

293
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:02,670
Honey!

294
00:15:03,670 --> 00:15:04,550
Where are you going?

295
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:06,030
Where's Erlang? I'll go find him.

296
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:07,030
Don't go.

297
00:15:07,030 --> 00:15:07,590
Go back to your room.

